contentrichtext.text: The '''National Automated Fingerprint Identification System''' (NAFIS) was established in [[Australia]] in 1986, an upgraded system commenced operations in April 2001 and provides technological improvements in fingerprint matching for use by [[Law enforcement in Australia|law enforcement]] agencies. ==External links== *[http://www.crimtrac.gov.au/systems___projects_national_automated_fingerprint_identification_system__nafis_.html] {{Wayback|date=20080229123852|url=http://www.crimtrac.gov.au/systems___projects_national_automated_fingerprint_identification_system__nafis_.html|df=yes}} [[Category:Law enforcement in Australia]] {{Australia-gov-stub}}
